2.1. Prerequirements: Validation of Instruments, Supplies, and Reagents and Personnel Qualification. According to GMP guidelines [1] , validation of instruments, supplies, and reagents have been performed as already described [11] . Briefly, the instruments were subjected to installation qualification (IQ), in accordance with the manufacturer specifications and to operational qualification (OQ). Reagents upon receipt were properly checked against specifications and recorded. Authorized GMP staff for quality control department follows a continuous training program. Duties of the personnel involved in quality control procedures and quality control manager's responsibilities were clearly described in written analytical protocols and in job description, as requested by the GMP guidelines. 


